GEMINI-CURSES(1)           User Commands           GEMINI-CURSES(1)

NAME
    gemini-curses - ncurses terminal interface for the Gemini API

SYNOPSIS
    gemini-curses
    gemini-curses <session_name>
    gemini-curses --resume <session_name>
    gemini-curses --list
    gemini-curses --models
    gemini-curses --autoscan-model
    gemini-curses --version
    gemini-curses --help

DESCRIPTION
    gemini-curses is a Python ncurses interface for Gemini. It is the
    full-screen terminal interface companion to the Bash gemini-cli tool.

    It provides:
        - scrollable transcript area
        - multiline input box
        - wrapped input display
        - proper cursor movement
        - named and resumable sessions
        - timestamped logs
        - rolling memory context
        - attachment extraction for code blocks
        - in-app model selection
        - in-app model autoscan
        - in-app API key entry

USAGE
    First-time setup:

        gemini-curses
            Then press F3 to paste an API key.
            Then press F4 to autoscan for a working model.

    Start a normal timestamped chat:

        gemini-curses

    Start a named full-screen chat:

        gemini-curses android-backup

    Resume a named chat:

        gemini-curses --resume android-backup

    List saved chats:

        gemini-curses --list

    List currently available Gemini models:

        gemini-curses --models

    Find a working model from the shell:

        gemini-curses --autoscan-model

    Use the in-app model tools:

        F2    manual model selector
        F4    autoscan for working model

SESSION MANAGEMENT
    gemini-curses
        Start a new timestamped session.

    gemini-curses <name>
        Start or open a named session.

    gemini-curses --resume <name>
        Resume an existing named session. If the session does not exist,
        the command exits with an error.

    gemini-curses --list
        List saved sessions.

    gemini-curses --models
        List available Gemini models that support generateContent, then exit.

    gemini-curses --autoscan-model
        Fetch the current model list, test each generateContent-compatible
        model with a minimal prompt, and print the first working model ID to
        standard output. Progress is printed to standard error.

    gemini-curses --version
        Display version information.

    gemini-curses --help
        Display built-in help.

CONTROLS
    Enter
        Insert newline in the input box.

    Ctrl+G
    F5
        Send the current message.

    F2
        Open the in-app model selector. The selector retrieves the model list
        from the Gemini models endpoint and activates the selected model for
        the current program run.

        Press i inside the selector to view metadata for the highlighted
        model, including display name, API name, token limits, supported
        methods, and description.

        After selecting a model, the user is offered the option to save it to
        the config file as MODEL=<model_id>.

    F3
        Open the API-key input dialog. The pasted key is activated for the
        current program run only. It is not written to the config file.

    F4
        Run model autoscan. The tool fetches the live model list, tests
        generateContent-compatible models in API-returned order, activates
        the first model that returns usable text, and offers to save it to
        the config file.

    F10
    Ctrl+Q
        Quit the interface.

    PgUp
        Scroll transcript upward.

    PgDn
        Scroll transcript downward.

    Arrow keys
        Move cursor inside the input box or navigate selectors.

    Home
    End
        Move cursor to beginning or end of current input line.

    Ctrl+U
        Clear current input.

    Ctrl+L
        Redraw screen.

    Tab
        Insert four spaces.

MODEL DISCOVERY
    Available Gemini models can be listed from the command line:

        gemini-curses --models

    They can also be listed directly with curl:

        curl "https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/models?key=YOUR_API_KEY"

    Inside the ncurses interface, press F2 to open the model selector.

    The selector shows model IDs and metadata returned by the API. The tool
    does not claim to know the best model permanently because Google's model
    list may change.

MODEL AUTOSCAN
    Model autoscan is intended for users who do not know which model to pick.

    From the shell:

        gemini-curses --autoscan-model

    Inside the interface:

        F4

    Autoscan performs the following steps:

        1. Fetch the live Gemini model list.
        2. Filter to models that support generateContent.
        3. Test each candidate with a minimal prompt:
               Reply with OK.
        4. Activate the first model that returns valid text.

    Autoscan does not guarantee the best model. It only finds a functional
    text-generation model available to the current API key.

    Autoscan may consume multiple API calls.

CONFIGURATION
    Configuration file:
        ~/.config/gemini-cli/config

    The ncurses version intentionally uses the same configuration file as
    the Bash version.

    Supported keys:

        MODEL
            Gemini model identifier.

            If MODEL is not configured, gemini-curses labels
            gemini-2.5-flash as a fallback model. This is not a promise that
            the fallback is best or permanently available.

            Use F4 or --autoscan-model to find a currently working model.

        HISTORY_LIMIT
            Number of recent conversation entries retained in memory.
            Default: 12

        GEMINI_API_KEY
            Optional API key. Environment variable takes priority.

        SESSION_DIR
            Directory used for session log storage.
            Default: ~/.gpt

        ATTACHMENT_DIR
            Directory used for extracted code artifacts.
            Default: SESSION_DIR/attachments

ENVIRONMENT
    GEMINI_API_KEY
        Preferred API key source.

        Precedence:
            1. Environment variable
            2. Config file
            3. F3 runtime API-key input

    The F3 API-key input feature is session-only. It does not save the key
    to disk.

FILES
    ~/.config/gemini-cli/config
        Configuration file.

    SESSION_DIR/*.log
        Session log files.

    ATTACHMENT_DIR/
        Extracted code block attachments.

ATTACHMENT SYSTEM
    Markdown fenced code blocks returned by Gemini are extracted from
    terminal display and saved into ATTACHMENT_DIR.

    The original raw Gemini response remains preserved in the session log.

    File names follow this pattern:

        <session>-<type>-NN.<extension>

    Examples:

        android-backup-python-01.py
        linux-help-bash-02.sh
        notes-json-01.json

SESSION NAMES
    Session names are sanitized for filesystem safety.

    Characters outside letters, numbers, dot, dash, and underscore are
    converted to underscores.

MEMORY MODEL
    gemini-curses keeps a rolling conversation context in memory.

    When resuming an existing session, the tool rebuilds recent memory from
    the session log and displays recent log entries in the transcript window.

LIMITATIONS
    - Requires Python 3 with curses support
    - Requires internet access
    - API quota restrictions apply
    - Autoscan may consume multiple API calls
    - F3 API-key input is not persistent
    - F2 model selection is persistent only if saved when prompted
    - F4 autoscan model selection is persistent only if saved when prompted
    - No mouse support in this release

VERSION
    gemini-curses version 0.3.0

